import numpy as np
import cv2
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
In [10]:
img = cv2.imread('che.jpg', 0)

dft = cv2.dft(np.float32(img), flags=cv2.DFT_COMPLEX_OUTPUT)
dft_shift = np.fft.fftshift(dft)

magnitude_spectrum = 20 * np.log(cv2.magnitude(dft_shift[:, :, 0], dft_shift[:, :, 1]))

rows, cols = img.shape
crow, ccol = int(rows / 2), int(cols / 2)

# Concentric BPF mask (other shapes are welcome).
rows, cols = img.shape
crow, ccol = int(rows / 2), int(cols / 2)

mask = np.zeros((rows, cols, 2), np.uint8)
r_out = 50 # outside radius of the mask
r_in = 10 # inside radius of the mask
center = [crow, ccol]
x, y = np.ogrid[:rows, :cols]

mask_area = np.logical_and(((x - center[0]) ** 2 + (y - center[1]) ** 2 >= r_in ** 2),
                           ((x - center[0]) ** 2 + (y - center[1]) ** 2 <= r_out ** 2))
mask[mask_area] = 1

dft = cv2.dft(np.float32(img), flags=cv2.DFT_COMPLEX_OUTPUT)
dft_shift = np.fft.fftshift(dft)

fshift = dft_shift * mask

fshift_mask_mag = 2000 * np.log(cv2.magnitude(fshift[:, :, 0], fshift[:, :, 1]))

f_ishift = np.fft.ifftshift(fshift)
img_back = cv2.idft(f_ishift)
img_back = cv2.magnitude(img_back[:, :, 0], img_back[:, :, 1])

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1), plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
plt.title('Original Image'), plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([])
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2), plt.imshow(magnitude_spectrum, cmap='gray')
plt.title('FFT Transformed'), plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([])
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3), plt.imshow(fshift_mask_mag, cmap='gray')
plt.title('FFT + Mask'), plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([])
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4), plt.imshow(img_back)
plt.title('iFFT Transformed'), plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([])
plt.show()

for i in range(1,5):
    for j in range(1,5):
        num = 1
        mask = np.zeros((rows, cols, 2), np.uint8)
        r_out = 10*i
        r_in = 2*j
        center = [crow, ccol]
        x, y = np.ogrid[:rows, :cols]

        mask_area = np.logical_and(((x - center[0]) ** 2 + (y - center[1]) ** 2 >= r_in ** 2),
                                   ((x - center[0]) ** 2 + (y - center[1]) ** 2 <= r_out ** 2))
        mask[mask_area] = 1

        dft = cv2.dft(np.float32(img), flags=cv2.DFT_COMPLEX_OUTPUT)
        dft_shift = np.fft.fftshift(dft)

        fshift = dft_shift * mask

        fshift_mask_mag = 2000 * np.log(cv2.magnitude(fshift[:, :, 0], fshift[:, :, 1]))

        f_ishift = np.fft.ifftshift(fshift)
        img_back = cv2.idft(f_ishift)
        img_back = cv2.magnitude(img_back[:, :, 0], img_back[:, :, 1])

        plt.imshow(img_back)
        plt.title('r_out: {} r_in: {}'.format(i, j)), plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([])
        plt.show()
